headline: UDR: Q1 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The Highlands Ranch, Colorado-based real estate investment trust said it had funds from operations of $219.1 million, or 61 cents per share, in the period. The average estimate of nine analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of 61 cents per share. Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry.

headline: UDR Announces First Quarter 2025 Results and Reaffirms Full-Year 2025 Guidance Ranges
summary: DENVER, April 30, 2025--UDR, Inc. (the "Company") (NYSE: UDR), announced today its first quarter 2025 results. Net Income, Funds from Operations ("FFO"), and FFO as Adjusted ("FFOA") per diluted share for the quarter ended March 31, 2025, are detailed below.
